The position of the Ile132 was studied in the same model of human PGM3 as was earlier described [14] (Fig. 2
). Since human PGM3 protein has not been crystallized yet, the best model available is based on the X-ray structure of Pgm3 from A. fumigatus
[18]. In this homology model Ile322 is located in the end of the β-sheet in the sugar-binding domain (domain 3), and seems to be engaged in hydrophobic contacts that likely contribute to the stability of the domain. The Ile322Thr substitution may therefore have a destabilizing effect on the three dimensional structure of the protein.
